

PROJECT REPORT

Medication Reminder App (Python)

1. Introduction

This project is a simple Python-based medication reminder app. Its goal is to help people remember to take their medicines on time. The program displays reminders at fixed intervals and supports multiple languages using small JSON files.

2. Objective

To create a basic automated reminder system

To allow users to choose their preferred language

To make the system simple, reliable, and easy to use

3. How the Project Works

The project contains a Python script and a folder with language files.
When the program starts:

1. The user selects a language (like English or Bengali).


2. The program loas the reminder message from the matching JSON file.


3. It shows the reminder in the selected language.


4. It repeats this reminder automatically after a fixed number of hours.

4. Key Components

Python 3

Uses simple libraries: time, json, os

JSON files store remnders like:


5. Features

Multilingual reminders

Runs automatically in a loop

Lightweight and beginner-friendly

Works on any device with Python

6. Advantages

Helps maintain a regular medication routine

Very easy to set up

Flexible and customizable


7. Limitations

Works in a terminal only (no GUI)

Needs to keep running in the background


8. Future Improvements

Add popup notifications

Add text-to-speech reminders

Add WhatsApp/Telegram alerts

Create a full GUI 

9. Conclusion

This project shows how Python can be used to build simple automation tools that make life easier. The reminder system is easy to use, customizable, and helpful for anyone who needs regular medication reminders.


